  "prompt": "What is the weather in Orlando like on June, and how does it differ from the weather in August?",
  "response": "In Orlando, Florida, the weather in June and August is typically hot and humid, but there are some differences between the two months.\n\n**June Weather in Orlando:**\n\n- **Temperature:** Average high temperatures in June are around 89\u00b0F (32\u00b0C), while average lows are around 72\u00b0F (22\u00b0C).\n- **Rainfall:** June marks the beginning of the rainy season in Orlando. The city experiences an average of 7.39 inches (188 mm) of rainfall spread over about 16 days. Afternoon thunderstorms are common.\n- **Humidity:** Humidity levels are high, often making the temperature feel even warmer.\n\n**August Weather in Orlando:**\n\n- **Temperature:** Average high temperatures in August are around 91\u00b0F (33\u00b0C), and average lows are around 74\u00b0F (23\u00b0C). This makes August slightly warmer than June.\n- **Rainfall:** August is typically wetter than June, with an average of 7.52 inches (191 mm) of rainfall over about 18 days. The frequency of afternoon thunderstorms remains high.\n- **Humidity:** Humidity levels remain high, similar to June, contributing to the heat index.\n\n**Key Differences:**\n\n- **Temperature:** August is slightly warmer than June, both in terms of average highs and lows.\n- **Rainfall:** August tends to be a bit wetter than June, with more days experiencing rain.\n- **Overall Feel:** Both months are hot and humid, but August can feel more oppressive due to the higher temperatures and slightly increased rainfall.\n\nIn summary, while both June and August in Orlando are characterized by hot, humid conditions and frequent afternoon thunderstorms, August tends to be warmer and wetter than June.",
